[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubprocess command returned a non-zero exit status: [0m[1;36m1[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mINFO:__main__:Running: docker run --privileged --shm-[0m[33msize[0m[39m=[0m[35m2g[0m[39m --platform linux/amd64[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--rm -i -e [0m[33mHELPER[0m[39m=[0m[3;92mTrue[0m[39m -e [0m[33mARCHITECTURE[0m[39m=[0m[35mx86_64[0m[39m -v [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/qqor/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mlibexif[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mout[0m[39m -v [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmppe2prxb7[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_from_data_fuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA heap-buffer-overflow vulnerability has been detected in the libexif library [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mduring fuzzing operations. The issue occurs when processing EXIF data, specifically[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min the `exif_data_load_data_entry` function, which attempts to read [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes beyond[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe allocated heap buffer boundary. The vulnerability was discovered using [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer during fuzzing with the `exif_from_data_fuzzer`.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Issue Overview[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzing operation triggered an AddressSanitizer error indicating a [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow with a READ operation of [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes at address `[0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[39m`.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis address is located [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m bytes after a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte region allocated on the heap, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmeaning the read operation attempted to access memory immediately beyond the valid [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocated buffer.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Vulnerability Type[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis is a **heap-buffer-overflow** vulnerability, specifically a multi-byte read [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moperation that exceeds the bounds of an allocated heap buffer. The SCARINESS score [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof [0m[1;36m26[0m[39m indicates this is a medium-severity issue with the classification [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"multi-byte-read-heap-buffer-overflow"[0m[39m.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Stack Trace Analysis[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe vulnerability manifests through the following call chain:[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Entry Point**: `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` in [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[35m/src/[0m[95mexif_from_data_fuzzer.cc[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m51:16[0m[39m` - The fuzzer harness that feeds test data to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe library[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **API Call**: `exif_data_new_from_data` in [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[35m/src/libexif/libexif/[0m[95mexif-data.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m159:2[0m[39m` - Creates new EXIF data structure from raw[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdata[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Data Loading**: `exif_data_load_data` in [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[35m/src/libexif/libexif/[0m[95mexif-data.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m984:2[0m[39m` - Loads and parses EXIF data[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Content Processing**: `exif_data_load_data_content` in [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[35m/src/libexif/libexif/[0m[95mexif-data.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m531:8[0m[39m` - Processes EXIF content sections[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Vulnerable Function**: `exif_data_load_data_entry` in [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[35m/src/libexif/libexif/[0m[95mexif-data.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m213:3[0m[39m` - The function where the actual buffer [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow occurs[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Memory Operation**: `__asan_memcpy` - The memory copy operation that triggered[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe overflow detection[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Memory Allocation Details[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Allocated Region**: [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m bytes starting at address `[0m[1;36m0x511000000180[0m[39m`[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Region End**: `[0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m207[0m[39m bytes from start[0m[1;39m)[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Overflow Location**: Attempt to read [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes starting at `[0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[39m`, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhich is exactly at the boundary [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m0[0m[39m bytes after the allocated region ends[0m[1;39m)[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Shadow Byte**: `[0m[1;36m07[0m[39m` indicates [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m bytes are partially addressable at the overflow[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlocation[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Key Observations[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Precise Boundary Overflow**: The overflow occurs exactly at the end of the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocated buffer, suggesting insufficient bounds checking when calculating read [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msizes or offsets in `exif_data_load_data_entry`.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **memcpy Operation**: The vulnerability is triggered during a `memcpy` [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moperation, indicating the code is attempting to copy data without proper validation[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof the source buffer size.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **EXIF Entry Processing**: The issue occurs specifically during the loading of [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindividual EXIF data entries, which suggests problems in parsing entry metadata or [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalculating entry data sizes.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas for Investigation[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo gain a holistic understanding of this vulnerability, the following parts of the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcodebase should be investigated:[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **`[0m[35m/src/libexif/libexif/[0m[95mexif-data.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;36m213[0m[39m`**: The exact line where [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry` performs the memcpy operation - examine how the copy [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msize is calculated and validated.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **`exif_data_load_data_entry` function**: Review the complete implementation to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munderstand:[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How entry sizes are determined from EXIF metadata[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - What bounds checking is performed before memory operations[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How offsets into the source buffer are calculated[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **`exif_data_load_data_content` function [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m531[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**: Understand how this [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction iterates through EXIF entries and passes data to [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry`.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **`exif_data_load_data` function**: Review the overall data loading logic to [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munderstand buffer management and size tracking.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **EXIF Data Format Parsing**: Investigate how the library parses EXIF header [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstructures and entry metadata, particularly:[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Tag type and size calculations[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Offset calculations within the EXIF data[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Validation of entry counts and sizes against available buffer space[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Buffer Size Tracking**: Examine how the original data size is tracked and [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalidated throughout the parsing process to ensure sufficient data is available for[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39meach operation.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m412[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m * recursion as well as the potential for worst-case future [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrecursive[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m413[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m * calls. Since it's difficult to tell ahead of time how often [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrecursion[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m414[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m * will occur, this assumes the worst by assuming every tag could [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mend up[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m415[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m * causing recursion.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m416[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m * The value of [0m[1;36m170[0m[39m was chosen to limit typical EXIF structures to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m417[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m * recursive depth of about [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m, but pathological ones [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthose with [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvery[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m418[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m * many tags[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to only [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m419[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m420[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mexif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_CORRUPT_DATA, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m421[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m  [0m[32m"Deep/expensive recursion detected!"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m422[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m423[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m424[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m425[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Read the number of entries *[0m[35m/[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m426[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset, ds, [0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m427[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mexif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_CORRUPT_DATA, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m428[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m  [0m[32m"Tag data past end of buffer [0m[32m([0m[32m%u+2 > %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, offset, ds[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m429[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m409[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[35m/[0m[39m*[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m410[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m * recursion_cost is a logarithmic-scale indicator of how expensive[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthis[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m411[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m * recursive call might end up being. It is an indicator of the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdepth of[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m412[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m * recursion as well as the potential for worst-case future [0m        [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m294[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39mexif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mne->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG,[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m295[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[32m"ExifMnoteCanon"[0m[39m,[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m296[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[32m"Tag data past end of buffer [0m[32m([0m[32m%u > %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m,[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m297[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[1;39m([0m[39munsigned[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdataofs + s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, buf_size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m298[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39mcontinue;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m299[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m300[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m301[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39mn->entries[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mtcount[0m[1;39m][0m[39m.data = exif_mem_alloc [0m[1;39m([0m[39mne->mem, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m302[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!n->entries[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mtcount[0m[1;39m][0m[39m.data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m303[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[1;35mEXIF_LOG_NO_MEMORY[0m[1;39m([0m[39mne->log, [0m[32m"ExifMnoteCanon"[0m[39m, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m48[0m[39m:     [0m[1;39m{[0m[39mEXIF_FORMAT_DOUBLE,    [0m[1;35mN_[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Double"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,    [0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m,[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m49[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m{[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, NULL, [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Root Cause Analysis[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter thorough analysis of the code snippets and evaluation report, I've identified[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe precise root cause of the heap-buffer-overflow:[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe vulnerability exists in the `exif_data_load_data_entry` function [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mlibexif/exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:163[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m236[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, which reads a [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m-byte EXIF entry header from the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer **without first validating** that these [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m bytes are within the buffer [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mboundaries.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Specific Issue[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mLines [0m[1;36m170[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m172[0m[39m unconditionally read the entry header:[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `entry->tag = [0m[1;35mexif_get_short[0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` - reads [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m bytes at offset+[0m[1;36m0[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `entry->format = [0m[1;35mexif_get_short[0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m, [0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` - reads [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m bytes at offset+[0m[1;36m2[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `entry->components = [0m[1;35mexif_get_long[0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m, [0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` - reads [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes at [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moffset+[0m[1;36m4[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mLine [0m[1;36m193[0m[39m conditionally reads:[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `doff = [0m[1;35mexif_get_long[0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, [0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` - reads [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes at offset+[0m[1;36m8[0m[39m when s > [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Total**: Up to [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m bytes are read from `d + offset` through `d + offset + [0m[1;36m11[0m[39m`, but[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthere is **NO CHECK** ensuring `offset + [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m <= size` before these reads.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe existing bounds checks at lines [0m[1;36m198[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m204[0m[39m only validate the entry's DATA [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mportion [0m[1;39m([0m[39musing `doff` and `s`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, not the entry [0m[1;33mHEAD[0m[39mER itself.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Evidence from Codebase[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThree other functions in the libexif codebase demonstrate the CORRECT pattern:[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **`exif_mnote_data_olympus_load`** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m437[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Uses `[0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39mo, buf_size, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m12[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` before reading entry header[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **`exif_mnote_data_canon_load`** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m251[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Uses `[0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39mo, buf_size, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m12[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` before reading entry header[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **`exif_data_load_data_thumbnail`** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m333[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Uses `CHECKOVERFLOW` before [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmemcpy operation[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAll three functions follow the defensive programming pattern that is missing in [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry`.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Primary Fix [0m[1;39m([0m[39mCRITICAL - Resolves the Heap-Buffer-Overflow[0m[1;39m)[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location**: libexif/exif-data.c, function `exif_data_load_data_entry`[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Action**: Insert bounds check immediately after line [0m[1;36m168[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mafter variable [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeclarations, before first buffer read at line [0m[1;36m170[0m[1;39m)[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Code to insert**:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[39m* Validate that we can read the [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m-byte entry header *[0m[35m/[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset, size, [0m[1;36m12[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    exif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              [0m[32m"Short entry header [0m[32m([0m[32m%u + 12 > %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, offset, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Rationale**:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The CHECKOVERFLOW macro [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefined at line [0m[1;36m51[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m safely validates: `[0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset >= size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m|| [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m12[0m[39m > size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset > size - [0m[1;36m12[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This ensures all three conditions for safe access: offset is valid, size is [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msufficient, and offset + [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m doesn't exceed size[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The macro avoids integer overflow by using subtraction instead of addition[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Returning [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m causes the caller [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m531[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m533[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to skip this entry, which is the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mappropriate behavior[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This matches the pattern used consistently in Canon and Olympus MakerNote loaders[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Secondary Fix [0m[1;39m([0m[39mRECOMMENDED - Defense in Depth[0m[1;39m)[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location**: libexif/exif-data.c, function `exif_data_load_data_entry`[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Action**: Replace lines [0m[1;36m183[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m186[0m[39m with improved integer overflow detection[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Current code** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m183[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m186[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ms = [0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->format[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m * entry->components;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39ms < entry->components[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m{[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Replacement**:[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ms = [0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->format[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m * entry->components;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[39m* Check for integer overflow in size calculation *[0m[35m/[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->format[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m &&[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    size [0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->format[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m < entry->components[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    exif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_CORRUPT_DATA, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              [0m[32m"Tag size overflow detected [0m[32m([0m[32m%u * %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              [0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->format[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, entry->components[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    exif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_CORRUPT_DATA, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              [0m[32m"Zero tag size"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Rationale**:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Uses division to detect overflow: `size [0m[35m/[0m[39m format_size < components` is equivalent[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto `format_size * components > size` but avoids multiplication overflow[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This pattern is used in Canon MakerNote loader [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m268[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m273[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and Olympus [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMakerNote loader [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m460[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m465[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- More robust than checking `s < entry->components`, which misses certain overflow [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatterns[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Provides consistent behavior across the codebase[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Why This is the Optimal Approach[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Targets Root Cause**: Directly addresses the missing bounds check that allows [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mout-of-bounds reads[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Minimal Impact**: Only adds validation; doesn't change logic for valid data[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Consistent with Codebase**: Follows patterns already established in Canon and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mOlympus MakerNote loaders[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Defensive Programming**: Makes the function safe regardless of caller [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39massumptions[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Preserves Functionality**: Valid EXIF data continues to work; only malformed [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdata is rejected[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### How It Preserves Existing Logic[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **No API Changes**: Function signature and return semantics unchanged[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Error Handling**: Return value of [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m is already properly handled by caller [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m531[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m533[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Logging**: Uses existing logging infrastructure [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexif_log[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m for debugging[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Processing Continues**: Other valid entries continue to be processed; only [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproblematic ones are skipped[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Backward Compatible**: No breaking changes for valid EXIF data[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### How It Addresses the Evaluation Report[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Prevents Heap-Buffer-Overflow**: The check catches attempts to read beyond [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer boundaries before they occur[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Exact Boundary Protection**: Validates that all [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m bytes of the entry header [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare readable, addressing the [0m[32m"0 bytes after region"[0m[39m overflow[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **[0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-Byte Read Issue**: While the crash reports a [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-byte read, this is likely [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdue to compiler optimization or alignment in the memcpy. The root cause is reading [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m-byte header followed by using those [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpotentially corrupted[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m values in [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubsequent operations[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Fuzzing Safety**: Handles malformed fuzzer input gracefully by detecting and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrejecting entries at invalid positions[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Side Effects and Mitigation[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Potential Side Effects**:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Malformed EXIF data that previously crashed will now be rejected with a log [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmessage[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Files with corrupted entry positions will have those entries skipped[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Mitigation**:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This is the DESIRED behavior - corrupted data should be rejected, not processed[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Only affects invalid/malformed data; valid EXIF files are unaffected[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Aligns with security best practices for input validation[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Consistent with how similar libraries handle corrupt data[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Similar Solutions in Codebase[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fix directly mirrors existing implementations:[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Olympus MakerNote** [0m[1;39m([0m[39molympus/exif-mnote-data-olympus.[0m[1;92mc:437[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```c[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39mo, buf_size, [0m[1;36m12[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m, [0m[32m"Short MakerNote"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       break;[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Canon MakerNote** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcanon/exif-mnote-data-canon.[0m[1;92mc:251[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```c[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39mo, buf_size, [0m[1;36m12[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m, [0m[32m"Short MakerNote"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       break;[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Thumbnail Loading** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexif-data.[0m[1;92mc:333[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```c[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39mo, ds, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m, [0m[32m"Bogus thumbnail size..."[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       return;[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThese demonstrate that the pattern is well-established and trusted in the codebase.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Implementation Steps[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Apply Primary Fix**:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Open libexif/exif-data.c[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Locate function `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m163[0m[1;39m)[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After line [0m[1;36m168[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`unsigned int s, doff;`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, insert the bounds check[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Before line [0m[1;36m170[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfirst `entry->tag` read[0m[1;39m)[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Apply Secondary Fix** [0m[1;39m([0m[39moptional but recommended[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In the same function[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Replace lines [0m[1;36m183[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m186[0m[39m with improved overflow detection[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Maintain the same error-handling behavior [0m[1;39m([0m[39mreturn [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Verification**:[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Compile with AddressSanitizer enabled[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Run the fuzzer test case that triggered the issue[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Verify no heap-buffer-overflow occurs[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Check that valid EXIF files still parse correctly[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Review debug logs to confirm rejected entries are logged appropriately[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Conclusion[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis fix strategy addresses the heap-buffer-overflow by adding the missing bounds [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcheck that validates the [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m-byte entry header can be safely read before accessing [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mit. The approach is conservative, well-established in the codebase, and maintains [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfull backward compatibility while significantly improving security against [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmalformed EXIF data.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mINFO:__main__:Running: docker run --privileged --shm-[0m[33msize[0m[39m=[0m[35m2g[0m[39m --platform linux/amd64[0m [2m                [0m
