[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/qqor/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mlibexif[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mout[0m[39m -v [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmppe2prxb7[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_from_data_fuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue reveals a heap-buffer-overflow vulnerability in the libexif [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibrary, specifically in the `exif_data_load_data_entry` function at line [0m[1;36m213[0m[39m of [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif-data.c`. The AddressSanitizer detected a READ of size [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m at address [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[39m`, which is located [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m bytes after a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte allocated region. A [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch was attempted to add validation checks for the entry header and to prevent [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minteger overflow in size calculations. However, after applying the patch, the same [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow error persists, now occurring at line [0m[1;36m231[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mshifted due to [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madded code[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, indicating that the patch did not successfully address the root cause [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof the vulnerability.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe heap-buffer-overflow occurs during the execution of the `exif_from_data_fuzzer`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith the following call stack:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. `__asan_memcpy` is called from `exif_data_load_data_entry` at line [0m[1;36m213[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. This is invoked by `exif_data_load_data_content` at line [0m[1;36m531[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Which is called by `exif_data_load_data` at line [0m[1;36m984[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Triggered by `exif_data_new_from_data` at line [0m[1;36m159[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Originating from the fuzzer harness `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe error indicates a READ of size [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m attempting to access memory at [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[39m`, which is immediately after the end of a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte heap-allocated [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mregion [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x511000000180[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The shadow byte at the problematic [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlocation shows `[0m[1;36m07[0m[39m`, indicating [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m bytes are partially addressable, but the read [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattempts to access [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes, causing an overflow.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe SCARINESS score of [0m[1;36m26[0m[39m indicates this is a multi-byte read heap-buffer-overflow,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhich is a significant security concern.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch added two main validation checks to the `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction:[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Entry Header Validation [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m170[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m175[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**: A check using the `CHECKOVERFLOW` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmacro to validate that a [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m-byte entry header can be safely read from the buffer at[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe given offset:[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```c[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset, size, [0m[1;36m12[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       exif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[32m"Short entry header [0m[32m([0m[32m%u + 12 > %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, offset, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Integer Overflow Protection [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m192[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m203[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**: Enhanced validation for size [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalculation that checks for integer overflow when multiplying format size by [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomponent count:[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```c[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->format[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m &&[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       size [0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->format[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m < entry->components[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       exif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_CORRUPT_DATA, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[32m"Tag size overflow detected [0m[32m([0m[32m%u * %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->format[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, entry->components[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       exif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_CORRUPT_DATA, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[32m"Zero tag size"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Result After Applying Patch[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch did not resolve the issue. The same heap-buffer-overflow error occurs, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith the following key differences:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The error now appears at line [0m[1;36m231[0m[39m instead of line [0m[1;36m213[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39man [0m[1;36m18[0m[39m-line shift due to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe added code[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The memory addresses and overflow characteristics remain identical[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The call stack is the same[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The DEDUP_TOKEN remains unchanged, confirming this is the same vulnerability[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis indicates that while the patch added validation checks before the overflow [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moccurs, it did not actually prevent the conditions that lead to the overflow. The [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalidation checks are either:[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Not being triggered by the problematic input[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Not comprehensive enough to catch the actual overflow condition[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Added in the wrong location relative to where the actual overflow occurs[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas for Further Investigation[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo achieve a comprehensive understanding of the issue, the following areas should [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbe investigated:[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **The `memcpy` operation at line [0m[1;36m231[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39moriginally [0m[1;36m213[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**: The exact location [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhere the overflow occurs needs detailed analysis to understand what data is being [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcopied, from where, and how the size is determined.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Data offset calculation**: The mechanism by which `doff` is calculated and how[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mit relates to the actual buffer boundaries needs examination, particularly around [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlines [0m[1;36m208[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m220[0m[39m in the original code.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **The `CHECKOVERFLOW` macro**: Its implementation and whether it correctly [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalidates the conditions needed to prevent the overflow.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **The relationship between `s` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcalculated size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and `doff` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata offset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**: The[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode calculates `s` but the overflow may be occurring when using `doff` to [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdetermine where to read data from.[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **The validation logic between lines [0m[1;36m206[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m230[0m[39m**: This section determines whether [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdata is inline [0m[1;39m([0m[39mstored in the entry itself[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m or referenced [0m[1;39m([0m[39mstored at an offset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand the boundary checks for both cases need scrutiny.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **The input data structure**: Understanding what values in the test case cause [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`offset`, `size`, `doff`, and `s` to have values that lead to the overflow would [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhelp identify the missing validation.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. **The `exif_data_load_data_content` function**: Since this is the caller, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munderstanding how it iterates through entries and manages offsets could reveal [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msystematic issues with boundary management.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Analysis[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter analyzing the code snippets and evaluation report, I've identified the root [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcause of the persistent heap-buffer-overflow:[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Root Cause[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe `exif_data_load_data_entry` function reads a [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m-byte EXIF entry header [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m170[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m172[0m[39m and potentially [0m[1;36m193[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m **without first validating** that [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m bytes can be [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msafely read from the buffer at the given offset. The reads occur at:[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Line [0m[1;36m170[0m[39m: `[0m[1;35mexif_get_short[0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` - reads bytes [0m[1;39m[[0m[39moffset, offset+[0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Line [0m[1;36m171[0m[39m: `[0m[1;35mexif_get_short[0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m, [0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` - reads bytes [0m[1;39m[[0m[39moffset+[0m[1;36m2[0m[39m, [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moffset+[0m[1;36m3[0m[1;39m][0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Line [0m[1;36m172[0m[39m: `[0m[1;35mexif_get_long[0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m, [0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` - reads bytes [0m[1;39m[[0m[39moffset+[0m[1;36m4[0m[39m, offset+[0m[1;36m7[0m[1;39m][0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Line [0m[1;36m193[0m[39m: `[0m[1;35mexif_get_long[0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, [0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` - reads bytes [0m[1;39m[[0m[39moffset+[0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moffset+[0m[1;36m11[0m[1;39m][0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Why the Previous Patch Failed[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe evaluation report states that the patch added validation at lines [0m[1;36m170[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m175[0m[39m, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhich should have been the correct location. However, the error persists at line [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m231[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m18[0m[39m lines shifted[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, suggesting one of these scenarios:[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. The validation check used incorrect parameters or logic[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. The validation didn't properly return/exit on failure[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. There's an edge case in the CHECKOVERFLOW macro evaluation[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. The line numbers in the patch description don't match the actual code location[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mLooking at the error details:[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The heap-buffer-overflow occurs when trying to READ [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes at address [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m0x51100000024f[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The buffer is [0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x511000000180[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m = [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m bytes[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Reading at offset [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexactly at boundary + [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m indicates `doff = [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m` or nearby[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Reference Implementations[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBoth Canon and Olympus MakerNote parsers demonstrate the correct pattern:[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39mo, buf_size, [0m[1;36m12[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[39mlog, EXIF_LOG_CODE_CORRUPT_DATA, [0m[32m"Module"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"Short MakerNote"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    break; [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m or return[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Now safe to read entry header[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentry->tag = [0m[1;35mexif_get_short[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf + o, order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentry->format = [0m[1;35mexif_get_short[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf + o + [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m, order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentry->components = [0m[1;35mexif_get_long[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf + o + [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m, order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Step [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m: Add Entry Header Validation at Function Entry[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAt the very beginning of `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mimmediately after line [0m[1;36m168[0m[39m, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbefore line [0m[1;36m170[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, add:[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[39m* Validate that we can read the complete [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m-byte entry header *[0m[35m/[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset, size, [0m[1;36m12[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_CORRUPT_DATA, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[32m"Tag entry header overflows buffer [0m[32m([0m[32m%u + 12 > %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, offset, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Critical Details:**[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Use `EXIF_LOG_CODE_CORRUPT_DATA` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnot `EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to match the [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mseverity[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The check must be `[0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset, size, [0m[1;36m12[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` - validating that [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m bytes [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcan be read starting at `offset` within a buffer of `size`[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Must `return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m` immediately if check fails[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This validation ensures bytes [0m[1;39m[[0m[39moffset, offset+[0m[1;36m11[0m[1;39m][0m[39m are all accessible before any [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreads[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Step [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m: Enhance Integer Overflow Protection[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe existing check at line [0m[1;36m184[0m[39m `if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39ms < entry->components[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` needs to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbe more robust. After the entry header validation and before line [0m[1;36m183[0m[39m, add [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomprehensive overflow checks:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[39m* Validate format is within known range *[0m[35m/[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->format >= EXIF_FORMAT_COUNT[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_CORRUPT_DATA, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[32m"Invalid format value [0m[32m([0m[32m%u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, entry->format[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[39m* Calculate size with overflow protection *[0m[35m/[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munsigned int format_size = [0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->format[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mformat_size == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_CORRUPT_DATA, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[32m"Format has zero size [0m[32m([0m[32m%u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, entry->format[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[39m* Check multiplication won't overflow *[0m[35m/[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->components > [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m && format_size > UINT_MAX [0m[35m/[0m[39m entry->components[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_CORRUPT_DATA, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[32m"Tag size overflow [0m[32m([0m[32m%u * %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, format_size, entry->components[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Step [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m: Validate Data Offset Read[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBefore line [0m[1;36m193[0m[39m where we read the data offset, ensure we're not reading from out of[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbounds. The entry header validation covers this, but for defense in depth, add an [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39massertion comment:[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Safe to read offset field - validated by entry header check above *[0m[35m/[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    doff = [0m[1;35mexif_get_long[0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, data->priv->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    doff = offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Step [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m: Strengthen Inline Data Validation[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mFor the inline data case [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms ≤ [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, strengthen the validation at line [0m[1;36m195[0m[39m:[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter line [0m[1;36m195[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`doff = offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, before line [0m[1;36m198[0m[39m, add:[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[39m* For inline data, verify it's within the entry header we already validated *[0m[35m/[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* External data - doff points elsewhere, check it *[0m[35m/[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Inline data - must be within entry header bounds *[0m[35m/[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff, size, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_CORRUPT_DATA, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 [0m[32m"Inline tag data overflows [0m[32m([0m[32m%u + %u > %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, doff, s, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mWait, actually this is redundant since we already validate the entry header fits. [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mLet me reconsider[0m[33m...[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mActually, the inline data check is unnecessary if we've already validated the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m12[0m[39m-byte header. The inline data is always within bytes [0m[1;39m[[0m[39moffset+[0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, offset+[0m[1;36m11[0m[1;39m][0m[39m of the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentry, which is covered by the header validation.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Revised Step [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m: Simplify[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRemove the redundant inline data validation. The entry header validation at the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstart ensures bytes [0m[1;39m[[0m[39moffset, offset+[0m[1;36m11[0m[1;39m][0m[39m are readable, which covers all inline data [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcases.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Complete Fix Strategy [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSimplified[0m[1;39m)[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mApply these changes to `libexif/exif-data.c` in the `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction:[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Change [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m: Add Entry Header Validation [0m[1;39m([0m[39mAfter line [0m[1;36m168[0m[39m, before line [0m[1;36m170[0m[1;39m)[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[39m* Validate we can safely read the [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m-byte entry header *[0m[35m/[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset, size, [0m[1;36m12[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_CORRUPT_DATA, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[32m"Tag entry at offset %u would overflow buffer [0m[32m([0m[32msize %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             offset, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Change [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m: Enhanced Format and Size Validation [0m[1;39m([0m[39mAfter line [0m[1;36m172[0m[39m, before line [0m[1;36m183[0m[1;39m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[39m* Validate format value is in valid range *[0m[35m/[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->format >= EXIF_FORMAT_COUNT[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_CORRUPT_DATA, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[32m"Invalid format type %u in tag 0x%x"[0m[39m, [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             entry->format, entry->tag[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Change [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m: Strengthen Size Calculation [0m[1;39m([0m[39mReplace lines [0m[1;36m183[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m186[0m[1;39m)[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[39m* Calculate tag data size with overflow protection *[0m[35m/[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munsigned int format_size = [0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->format[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mformat_size == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Format with zero size - reject *[0m[35m/[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_CORRUPT_DATA, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[32m"Format %u has zero size"[0m[39m, entry->format[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[39m* Check for multiplication overflow: components * format_size *[0m[35m/[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->components > UINT_MAX [0m[35m/[0m[39m format_size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_CORRUPT_DATA, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[32m"Tag size overflow: %u components * %u bytes"[0m[39m, [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             entry->components, format_size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ms = format_size * entry->components;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_CORRUPT_DATA, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[32m"Tag has zero total size"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Why This is Optimal[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Follows Proven Pattern**: Matches the successful validation approach in [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCanon/Olympus parsers[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Defense in Depth**: Multiple layers of validation catch different error [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconditions[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Fail-Fast**: Validates before any reads, preventing garbage data propagation[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Comprehensive**: Covers entry header, format validity, and integer overflow[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Clear Error Messages**: Helps debugging and identifies specific failure points[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### How It Preserves Existing Logic[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All validations return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfailure[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m without modifying any data structures[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No changes to the core logic of reading entries or allocating memory[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Maintains the same API contract with callers[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Only adds early-exit paths for invalid input[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### How It Addresses the Issues[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Heap-buffer-overflow**: The entry header validation prevents reading beyond [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer bounds[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Integer overflow**: Enhanced checks prevent multiplication overflow in size [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalculation[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Invalid format**: Validation rejects out-of-range format values that could [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcause crashes[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Garbage data**: By validating before reads, prevents using invalid values in [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlater checks[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Potential Side Effects and Mitigation[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **More Strict Validation**: Some previously [0m[32m"accepted"[0m[39m malformed files may now be[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrejected[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Mitigation: This is correct behavior - malformed data should be rejected[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Performance**: Added checks add minimal overhead [0m[1;39m([0m[39ma few integer comparisons[0m[1;39m)[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Mitigation: These are trivial comparisons that prevent much more expensive [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcrashes[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Similar Solutions in Codebase[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis fix directly mirrors the validation patterns in:[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `libexif/olympus/exif-mnote-data-olympus.[0m[1;92mc:437[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m447[0m[39m` [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `libexif/canon/exif-mnote-data-canon.[0m[1;92mc:251[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m260[0m[39m`[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBoth use `[0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39mo, buf_size, [0m[1;36m12[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` before reading entry headers, proving [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthis approach works correctly in production code.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
